  "text": "## Upstream Connection Pool Overflow in Envoy v1.31.2\n\n### Definition of Overflow State\nThe overflow state is defined as an enum value in **envoy/common/conn_pool.h** (line 98), where `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` indicates that \"a resource overflowed and policy prevented a new connection from being created.\"\n\n### Where Overflow is Emitted\nThe overflow condition is emitted in **source/common/conn_pool/conn_pool_base.cc** in three key locations:\n\n1. **Connection Creation Overflow (Line 138)**: When a new connection cannot be created due to resource limits, `upstream_cx_overflow_` stat is incremented:\n   ```cpp\n   if (!can_create_connection) {\n     host_->cluster().trafficStats()->upstream_cx_overflow_.inc();\n   }\n   ```\n\n2. **Max Requests Overflow (Lines 175-179)**: In `attachStreamToClient()`, when the maximum request limit is reached:\n   ```cpp\n   if (enforceMaxRequests() && !host_->cluster().resourceManager(priority_).requests().canCreate()) {\n     ENVOY_LOG(debug, \"max streams overflow\");\n     onPoolFailure(client.real_host_description_, absl::string_view(),\n                   ConnectionPool::PoolFailureReason::Overflow, context);\n     traffic_stats.upstream_rq_pending_overflow_.inc();\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Pending Requests Overflow (Lines 282-287)**: In `newStreamImpl()`, when the pending request queue is full:\n   ```cpp\n   if (!host_->cluster().resourceManager(priority_).pendingRequests().canCreate()) {\n     ENVOY_LOG(debug, \"max pending streams overflow\");\n     onPoolFailure(nullptr, absl::string_view(), ConnectionPool::PoolFailureReason::Overflow,\n                   context);\n     host_->cluster().trafficStats()->upstream_rq_pending_overflow_.inc();\n   }\n   ```\n\n### Resource Manager Integration\n**source/common/upstream/resource_manager_impl.h** implements the `ResourceManagerImpl` class which enforces circuit breaker limits. The `canCreate()` method on resource limits determines whether the overflow condition occurs. This manager tracks:\n- `connections()` - connection limit\n- `pendingRequests()` - pending request queue limit  \n- `requests()` - concurrent request limit\n\n### HTTP and TCP Pool Implementations\nBoth **source/common/http/conn_pool_base.h** and **source/common/tcp/conn_pool.h** inherit from `ConnPoolImplBase` and implement the `onPoolFailure()` callback that handles the overflow event by invoking the caller's failure callback with the `PoolFailureReason::Overflow` reason.\n\n### Statistics\nThe overflow conditions are tracked via stats defined in **envoy/upstream/upstream.h** (ALL_CLUSTER_TRAFFIC_STATS macro):\n- `upstream_cx_overflow_` - Counter for connection pool overflows\n- `upstream_rq_pending_overflow_` - Counter for pending request queue overflows\n- `upstream_cx_pool_overflow_` - Counter for connection pool resource exhaustion\n\nThese statistics allow operators to detect and monitor upstream connection pool overflow during traffic spikes."
